# Bootstrap Instructions for {{ agent_name | title }}

## First-Time Setup

### 1. Verify SSH Key & GitHub Access
```bash
# Test GitHub SSH connection
ssh -T git@github.com

# List accessible repos
gh repo list infiquetra --limit 20
```

If SSH fails, generate and register a key:
```bash
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "{{ agent_email }}"
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
# Add to GitHub: https://github.com/settings/keys
```

### 2. Configure Git
```bash
git config --global user.name "{{ agent_name | title }}"
git config --global user.email "{{ agent_email }}"
git config --global init.defaultBranch main
```

### 3. GitHub CLI Authentication
```bash
gh auth status
# If not authenticated:
gh auth login --hostname github.com --web
```

### 4. Clone Infiquetra Repositories
```bash
mkdir -p ~/workspace/infiquetra

gh repo list infiquetra --limit 100 | while read -r repo _; do
    name=$(basename "$repo")
    gh repo clone "infiquetra/$name" ~/workspace/infiquetra/$name 2>/dev/null || true
done
```

### 5. Discord (Already Configured)
Your Discord bot token is pre-configured in OpenClaw. Verify it's connected:
- Check that OpenClaw gateway service is running: `sudo systemctl status openclaw-gateway`
- Look for your agent in Discord — it should show as online in the guild
- If offline: `sudo systemctl restart openclaw-gateway`

